    Zoo Rules PDF

    Uploaded by

    cristian villamizar
    0 ratings0% found this document useful (0 votes)

    1 page
    The code of practice for visitors to the zoo outlines several rules to ensure safety and protect the animals. Visitors must obey all signs and barriers, not feed or disturb the animals, and respect that the zoo is their home. Children under 16 must be accompanied by an adult. Radios, bikes, scooters and ball games are prohibited. Selfie sticks cannot be used past barriers and drones are strictly prohibited. Only service animals on leashes are allowed. Filming requires permission and litter must be disposed of properly. Hands should be washed and smoking is prohibited. Proper attire including shoes must be worn and solicitation is not allowed. Visitors may be escorted out for harmful or disruptive behavior and bags may be inspected.
